=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: Convert 3-(trifluoromethyl)aniline (Nc1cccc(C(F)(F)F)c1) to 1-(3-(trifluoromethyl)phenyl)urea, e.g. by carbamoylation with potassium cyanate/HCl (or via the corresponding aryl isocyanate then NH3), giving ArNHCONH2 where Ar = 3-CF3C6H4. | Step 2: Biginelli condensation of 1-(3-(trifluoromethyl)phenyl)urea + 4-cyanobenzaldehyde (N#Cc1ccc(C=O)cc1) + ethyl acetoacetate under acidic conditions to form the dihydropyrimidinone ester intermediate: ethyl 6-methyl-4-(4-cyanophenyl)-2-oxo-1-(3-(trifluoromethyl)phenyl)-1,2,3,4-dihydropyrimidine-5-carboxylate. | Step 3: Hydrolyze the ethyl ester (NaOH/H2O then acid workup, or LiOH) to the corresponding acid, furnishing the target CC1=C(C(=O)O)C(c2ccc(C#N)cc2)NC(=O)N1c1cccc(C(F)(F)F)c1.

